title: Red Curry Ramen Noodle Soup with Turkey and Butternut Squash
summary: Red Curry Ramen Noodle Soup with Turkey and Butternut Squash is a gluten free and dairy free soup. One serving contains 104 calories, 12g of protein, and 3g of fat. For $1.28 per serving, this recipe covers 14% of your daily requirements of vitamins and minerals. 3 people have tried and liked this recipe. It can be enjoyed any time, but it is especially good for Autumn. Head to the store and pick up chicken breast, fresh japanese ramen, roasted carrots, and a few other things to make it today. This recipe is typical of Indian cuisine. From preparation to the plate, this recipe takes about 20 minutes. All things considered, we decided this recipe deserves a spoonacular score of 63%. This score is solid. Try Crockpot Caramelized Pork Ramen Noodle Soup w/Curry Roasted Acorn Squash, Turkey Ramen Noodle Soup with Brussels Sprouts, and Butternut Squash Noodle Turkey Bolognese Stuffed Acorn Squash with Melted Gruyere: Two Ways for similar recipes.

winePairing.pairingText: Riesling, Sake, and Sauvignon Blanc are my top picks for Ramen Noodles. Saké is an obvious choice when it comes to Japanese food. If you want to stick to grape wine, though, you might opt for sauvignon blanc or riesling. The Bollig-Lehnert Piesporter Goldtroopfchen Riesling Spatlese with a 4.5 out of 5 star rating seems like a good match. It costs about 24 dollars per bottle.

productMatches.description: Full of ripe, tropical fruit flavors like pineapple, mango, and guava, with pastry accents. Offers a bright finish of kiwi fruit and lime, showing a touch of chamomile and cream.

instructions: In a large pot, bring the broth, red curry paste, garlic and ginger to a boil on medium-high heat.  Toss in the kale and allow to wilt for about a minute.  Add the cooked butternut squash, carrots and chickpeas.At this point you can also simply toss in the dried ramen noodles like I did by opening a packet of instant dried ramen noodles and discard the seasoning packets. Bring the pot to a boil and allow to simmer for 3 minutes.  Stir occasionally.  {Or if you are using any other type of noodles or would prefer to cook the ramen noodles separately, bring another pot of water to a boil and cook according to package instructions and drain and rinse under cold water.  Add the noodles into the pot of soup}Salt to taste and add in some cilantro and the lime juice.  Adjust flavors to your liking.Divide into bowls and garnish with some more fresh cilantro and scallions if desired.
